# RFC-0025

# Endpoint Advertisement Specification (EAS)

Status: Draft

Version: 0.1

Depends on:

* RFC-0015 Model Class Registry
* RFC-0023 Bundle Specification
* RFC-0024 Endpoint Manifest

---

# 1. Purpose

The Endpoint Advertisement Specification (EAS) defines the public information published by a Hypervisor for Endpoint discovery.

Endpoint Advertisements are optimized for efficient network discovery.

They intentionally expose only public information.

Implementation details remain private.

---

# 2. Design Principles

### EAS-1

Advertisement is a public projection of an Endpoint.

It is not the complete Endpoint Manifest.

---

### EAS-2

Advertisements contain only information required for routing, pricing and validation.

---

### EAS-3

Execution implementation remains private.

---

### EAS-4

Advertisements SHALL be cryptographically signed by the Hypervisor wallet.

---

# 3. Advertisement Structure

Every Advertisement SHALL contain:

```yaml id="q9kn4j"
advertisement:

  endpoint_id:

  owner_wallet:

  advertisement_id:

  timestamp:

  signature:
```

---

# 4. Public Identity

```yaml id="1xhfyy"
identity:

  display_name:

  model_class:

  capability:
```

Example:

```yaml id="69c7go"
identity:

  display_name: Opus4.6-class

  model_class: opus-class

  capability:

    - llm.chat
```

---

# 5. Endpoint Profile

The following Profile information MAY be published.

```yaml id="2lqvlt"
profile:

  summary:

  strengths:

  recommended_tasks:

  supported_languages:

  preferred_formats:
```

Profile information is advisory.

---

# 6. Pricing

Every Advertisement SHALL publish pricing information.

```yaml id="5w5q3j"
pricing:

  billing_unit:

  input_price:

  output_price:

  fixed_price:
```

Examples

LLM

```yaml id="6jkhki"
pricing:

  billing_unit: token

  input_price: 2.5

  output_price: 7.0
```

Speech-to-Text

```yaml id="lgn2sz"
pricing:

  billing_unit: second

  input_price: 0.4

  output_price: 0
```

Image Generation

```yaml id="7d80nf"
pricing:

  billing_unit: image

  fixed_price: 4.5
```

OCR

```yaml id="ggyt9t"
pricing:

  billing_unit: page

  fixed_price: 0.8
```

The Wallet computes settlement using Usage Events and Billing Units.

Advertisements never contain calculated prices.

---

# 7. Validation

```yaml id="rr14lq"
validation:

  status:

  validation_profile:

  observed_confidence:
```

Validation data are continuously updated by DAN.

---

# 8. Reputation

```yaml id="rnw6c4"
reputation:

  endpoint_score:

  hypervisor_score:

  confidence:
```

Reputation values are observations.

They are not operator declarations.

---

# 9. Configuration

```yaml id="vax6kb"
configuration:

  configuration_hash:

  bundle_hash:
```

ConfigurationHash uniquely identifies the observable execution configuration.

---

# 10. Availability

```yaml id="wkw38s"
availability:

  online:

  accepting_requests:

  estimated_queue:

  estimated_latency:
```

Availability values are dynamic.

---

# 11. Privacy

Advertisements SHALL NOT expose:

* Provider implementation
* Execution topology
* Local or remote execution
* Internal orchestration
* Provider chain
* Runtime architecture
* Internal resource allocation

---

# 12. Signature

Every Advertisement SHALL be signed using the Hypervisor Wallet.

The signature covers the entire Advertisement.

Consumers SHALL reject unsigned or invalid Advertisements.

---

# 13. Lifecycle

```text id="v07n1o"
Endpoint Updated

↓

Advertisement Generated

↓

Advertisement Signed

↓

Advertisement Published

↓

Registry Replication

↓

Discovery
```

---

# 14. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

Advertisements never expose implementation details.

---

Invariant 2

Advertisements expose observable properties only.

---

Invariant 3

Pricing is expressed using Billing Units.

---

Invariant 4

Reputation is observational.

---

Invariant 5

Advertisements are immutable once signed.

Any modification creates a new Advertisement.

---

# 15. Architectural Principle

The Endpoint Manifest represents the complete local configuration.

The Endpoint Advertisement represents the public network projection of that Endpoint.

Every Hypervisor is free to implement the Endpoint internally in any manner consistent with the published observable behavior.

This separation preserves execution privacy while enabling transparent discovery, pricing and verification across the AiDN network.
